Description:

Similar to the ls tool in UNIX, the grid ls tool allows the user to list entries in both local and RNS directories.

The following options are available:

-l | --long

Long format

-a | --all

Do not ignore entries starting with .

-e | --epr

Show the EPR of each RNS entry

-d | --directory

List directory entries instead of directory contents

-R | --recursive

List subdirectories recursively

-m | --multiline

Show a brief summary of the EPR of each RNS entry

--cert-chain
 
Show the certificates associated with each entry

-i | --date-information

Show the date created and date modified of each entry
